Sharing this live video for those of you who missed it! It includes the book reveal (as titled), also bonus Inki cat content, me chatting and making some sort of sense, and a peak at a surprise cake for Nabil’s bday (update: gave it to him that evening and he hadn’t guessed at all, yay!!!). Was so nice to say hi to all of you who popped in 💖
.
(Instagram doesn’t automatically flip the video over so all lettering looks backwards!!) 
.
.

node.text:
Just put together this video compiling sneak peak stuff from the book shoot! It’s almost two weeks of constant baking and creating (and was just before covid set in!) - very tiring but so satisfying seeing everything come together, and lots of fun thanks to the fabulous team ✨ I loved it! Thanks to all @quadrillebooks as well as the book shoot team: @celinebilliejean, @hebe_konditori , @ellisparrinder, @aliciajhouse @charliephillips, @danni_hair_makeup, @housecatillustration @marykatemcdevitt, @nabiltravels 💖
.
So exciting to see that it is now out in the world and sitting on some of your shelves! 💛thank you all! Please keep leaving lovely reviews on amazon, it’s really easy to do and helps me massively! 💛 have a lovely weekend xxx
.
.
.
.

node.text:
And the ingredients are down below for you ☺️ so I’ve made some standard naans with the dough, and then I also made a decorated naan because of course I couldn’t resist... plus the idea of a nan themed naan bread has been stuck in my head for months (as a in a nan aka a person). So thought I’d try it for the first time whilst filming myself 🤣 disclaimer: I didn’t really know any of my grandparents so this is not based on anyone in particular!!! Haha, probably shows too, cause I think I ended up making more of a gnome 🤪
.
Also these are yeasted naans but if you don’t have yeast, there’s lots of non yeasted recipes online :) This is mostly just for fun and to say hi to you all! I don’t know about you but my days are all merging into one mass of sleeping, eating, cats meowing, a little bit of baking, and quite a lot of gaming. So doing this video made me feel a bit more connected with it all! .
Here’s the dough ingredients:
360g plain flour ( or about 2 and 2/3 cup),
1/2tsp salt,
1/2tsp baking powder,
1tsp nigella seeds (optional),
7g fast action instant yeast,
100g water (or about 1/2 cup minus a tbsp),
150g milk or plant based milk (about 2/3 cup),
3tbsp yoghurt (dairy or plant based) .
For the butter mix:
100g butter/vegan butter (or about one stick)
Whole bulb garlic
fresh or frozen coriander (I used frozen which doesn’t look as good, but it tastes amazing!)
.
I actually originally developed this recipe to make vegan naan breads so that my friends could enjoy them, and they’ve gotten rave reviews!!! Hope you enjoy and tag me in any pics you make, as always I love seeing them!! 💖💖💖💖☺️ . P.s this makes a wet-ish dough but that means it’s so easy to stretch and bakes up light and fluffy. It’s tempting but you don’t want to be adding much more flour to it to make it easier to knead, just use as little as possible! 
.
.
.

Behind the scenes on the two week book shoot for my new book! I sort of look well chilled here but actually it was an intense two weeks of NON STOP BAKING - multitasking multiple bakes all at the same time. Bit like bake off (also have you seen the news that it’s back on 21st Sept woo🎉😍), in that you put your heart and soul in it and never stop baking, but a different kind of pressure cause no risk of being sent home phew, BUT got to make 50 or so bakes look on top form! Which is more than the 30 bakes i did for bake off!!! 😱 I was so busy I didn’t really get much video footage from the shoot, but just imagine that Phoenix cake but times many many times 🤓

Featuring @hebe_konditori @ellisparrinder @charlottelovely @danni_hair_makeup 🥰🥰🥰

node.text:
Growing older happens, but never lose touch of your inner child. I think the world tries to drill out your inner child, with its rules about what you should wear, how you should act sensibly, how you can get enthusiastic about stuff BUT not TOO enthusiastic.  Resist it!!! Go enjoy that bouncy castle and those balloons (two of my favourite things ever), wear all the colours and patterns you want, wear pyjamas in the day, run around barefoot, get food and paint all over yourself, sneak pieces off the top of a cake before it’s cut. Child-like is different to childish 💖 and the moments I feel child-like, are always the moments I feel utmost joy! 🌈
.
.
.

node.text: Ad Happy 8th birthday FINAL FANTASY XIV!!! 🥳 as promised, I have the recipe for my three-tiered FINAL FANTASY XIV cake - will put a swipe up link in my stories! It’s a long one, but flexible cause you can always just make just one tier, or just make some of the individual components like the Cactuar, Spriggan or Fat Chocobo (they’re tangzhong style and taste as fluffy as a chocobo!). Or make the whole thing, why not 💁🏻‍♀️ it was so fun making this and working out what types of bakes could bring to life each different creature, and a dream to do this for #FFXIV as I’ve loved the whole FINAL FANTASY franchise since I was a kid! Plus I feel a great affinity to Moogles 😀

Ad I’m obsessed with everything FINAL FANTASY, so when @squareenix and @ffxiv asked me to do a cake for #FFXIV ‘s 8th birthday, I was like YES OF COURSE! 😱😍The bottom tier is a sandy (biscuit) backdrop for the gingerbread Cactuars, the middle tier is a watercolour blue and white buttercream backdrop for the Fat Chocobos (made tangzhong sweet bread style!) and Spriggan (made from mochi filled with thick custard, decorated with tiny pieces of fondant, and holding kohakutou jelly ‘gems’), and the top tier cake is carved, covered with fondant and decorated as a Moogle ☺️
 
This is sneak peak version of the full version - and you can find the full version on youtube: (https://youtu.be/TcWqbFouU3o) - I’ll also put a swipe up link in my stories cause that’s easier! I loved creating this so so much as I grew up playing FINAL FANTASY games and it feels so much a part of my life 💖 recipe coming soon 😎

Robot fondant fancies!!! 🤖 - picture and recipe is in my new book ‘Celebrate with Kim-Joy’. I LOVE fondant fancies. And absolutely love making these, they’re so fun and endlessly customisable.  These are themed for Valentine’s Day as you can write custom messages on their screens for loved ones and friends. But really you can make them for birthdays, Christmas, New Years, loads of different celebrations! I also find the sprinkles and decorations are useful for distracting from any imperfections in the icing 😉 These have vegan and gluten free alternatives too!! Keep the preorders coming 😀😀😀🥳🥳🥳🥳 not too long to go now til release date ...!
Thanks to @ellisparrinder for this epic photo 📸💖

Something I really love is seeing you guys bake and just going for it, embracing unexpected results, mess and the whole process 🙌🏻 I really mean it when I say that I learn tons from you all! So thought in return I’d share my slightly imperfect but made with love mini cake I made for Nabil’s birthday - it was made in a rush and of course fruit +fondant doesn’t gel well, but it features fondant versions of my two favourite cute furry boys Inki and Mochi @kimjoyskittens - and it makes me smile, tastes amazing (light brown muscovado in a cake using the creaming method is dreamy!) and is full of happiness, so that’s all that matters 🙌🏻 

Also I really enjoyed my last live video doing the book reveal, felt like I really got over a fear there, and decided I’ve got to do another one!! This time doing a reveal of my new card game 🥳🥳🥳 what do you think? Maybe this weekend? I’ll try tell Inki and Mochi to attend too xx

Cake makes most surroundings a little bit brighter ☺️🍰 this wasn’t really my favourite picture of me out of the 20 or so Nabil took, but it’s the one where I’m happiest looking! And I usually want to put up pics of me where I look more real/smiley or have emotion, rather than skinnier or more conventionally attractive/posed etc... not that I’m always happy or smiling (far far from it! I definitely have my blah days! Quite a few recently 😩) but working towards being happier and true to myself is my main goal 💖 I think what I’m trying to say is smiling is a lovely thing, but you can smile if you want to, or don’t smile if you don’t want to - just be real, be vulnerable, and do what’s best for you! And wear better footwear than me when walking in rubble x
.
.
.

Got the chance to make one of these frog cakes last week, for a joint birthday celebration! 🐸🐸🐸 It’s all vegan: cinnamon and ginger cake, with salted caramel and biscoff buttercream between the layers, and vanilla buttercream around the outside. With vegan meringue, and the rest of the decorations is all buttercream. I wanted to put my own tweaks into the design - so spot the two tiny frogs, and the frog pretending to be a mushroom. I like the surreal feeling that you’re looking at a cake, but the frogs are in their world with their own mini frog cake. Will put a slicing video on my stories!! 
.
ALSO going live on here at in just under an hour (6pm U.K. time) to unwrap my new book for the first time ever, exciting!!! 🥳🥳🥳 say hi and ask me anything! (was going to be 8pm but changed as it’s Nabil bday and we’re going for a meal now!!).
.

The FIRST sneak peak into my new book...! This is a cake for the Day of the Dead 💀🌈 Probably one of the trickier looking recipes in there, but one of my favourites! And it’s not all that tricky - the line between the black and white is created using baking paper to stop the colour going over the line. And you do need to flip the whole cake over for the anti gravity drips, but once it’s been in the freezer for a bit, it’s easy!! The cake isn’t going anywhere! Like my other books, there are a selection of tasty cake recipes from red velvet to apple cake to creme brulee cake (including vegan and gluten free options!) that will work with this design, so you can pick your favourite. And just like before too, there aren’t just cakes - there’s bread, pastries, mousses, smaller bakes, biscuits, all sorts...! More to come soon. I have actually received the ACTUAL BOOK in the post the other day and resisted opening it so far as been thinking of doing an Instagram live for the first unwrapping, what do you think? Would you tune in? I’ve always had a bit of a mental block with Instagram lives cause of anxieties 😩, but I want to do it, I’m gonna do it!!!! ☺️
.
Photo by the ace @ellisparrinder (same as all my books cause he’s amazing!), and wonderful props by @charlottelovely, and the one and only fabulous baking buddy @hebe_konditori 🥰 published by @quadrillebooks 📚💖
.
.
.
